						<summary>

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 4[5], Śārvari, Āśvīja, huṇṇime, Śukravāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1120 October 8, Friday,</hi> when there was a lunar eclipse. <hi rend="bold">Durgarāja-Daṇḍanāyaka</hi> is stated to have granted some land for the service of the god Durgēśvara. His daughter <hi rend="bold">Chāvaṇadēvi</hi> is also said to have granted some land for the same purpose. The record is very much damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
